    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-01-14T18:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-01-14T18:36:00-05:00" n="779"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d779">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5867.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-14T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1913—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The dangerous situation at Acapulco would indicate necessity for prompt and
                    adequate protection on our part of American and foreign interests. I recommend
                    the immediate sending of war vessels adequate to meet the situation, with
                    instructions to remain in those waters and not to be withdrawn except after
                    consultation with the Embassy. I have meantime requested British Chargé
                    d’Affaires to detain English gunboat <hi rend="italic">Shearwater</hi> until our
                    Government shall have taken action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
